8/8/1936; Peru; 4-2; Austria; Hertha Platz, Berlin; T. Kristiansen
Alcalde 75, Villanueva 81, Villanueva 119, T.Fernandez 116; Werginz 22, Steinmetz 36
Peru: Valdivieso; A.Fernandes, V.Lavalle; Tovar, S.Castillo, Jordan; T.Alcalde, Magallanes, T.Fernandez, Villanueva, Morales.
Austria: E.Kainberger(cap); Kargl, Kunz; Krenn, Wallmuller, Hofmeister; Werginz, Laudon, Steinmetz, Kitzmuller, Fuchsberger. 
Notes: Upon protest by Austria this match was cancelled by the jury of appeal because peruvian fans had invaded the field to celebrate after Villanueva scored the 4th. goal in the last minute of the overtime, FIFA ordered the match replayed and Peru did not show because all their Olympia delegation had returned home in disagreement with the ruling.

